WEBVTT

00:24.354 --> 00:28.420
I knew I was gonna preach this sermon on June 17th, 2020.

00:28.460 --> 00:31.425
That's what I knew that I was gonna preach this sermon.

00:31.465 --> 00:35.291
And it took until now that I felt like it was the right time to preach it.

00:35.311 --> 00:39.397
And if you remember, at that time, COVID was in full force.

00:39.457 --> 00:41.100
We had just reopened the church.

00:41.120 --> 00:44.025
If you remember, we had just reopened the church.

00:44.165 --> 00:45.307
Crowds were limited.

00:45.327 --> 00:52.658
And at that time, we were still praying, God, I pray that our church as we opened is not part of a super spreader event.

00:52.898 --> 00:53.819
and praise God.

00:53.879 --> 00:55.181
We never were part of that.

00:55.882 --> 00:57.444
The economy was stalled.

00:58.145 --> 00:59.366
It was just a season.

00:59.386 --> 01:01.289
There were a lot of fear that was going.

01:01.309 --> 01:03.011
There was just fear in the air.

01:03.492 --> 01:12.644
And in the midst of this, our facilities director, Scott Olson, had died after a courageous battle against cancer.

01:13.165 --> 01:15.267
And we had prayed for him and prayed for him.

01:15.748 --> 01:20.434
And on the 17th, that was the day that we had his funeral.

01:20.994 --> 01:28.066
It was a very unusual June day because I believe it was 97 or 98 degrees that day.

01:28.587 --> 01:30.890
And we decided that we needed to have this funeral.

01:30.951 --> 01:36.219
We didn't know how to handle a funeral in COVID, but we knew we couldn't have it inside, so we were trying to figure out to do.

01:36.580 --> 01:42.770
So we actually had the funeral outside across the street from our Apple Valley campus at the gravesite.

01:42.790 --> 01:45.074
There were about 250 people there.

01:45.186 --> 01:58.556
And we were outside sweating, but it was the first time many of us had even been in a group that large, and people were showing up to honor him and to remember the life that he lived, and just to say to Leslie, we're there with you.

01:58.836 --> 02:01.362
She's on our staff as well, and so we were there.

02:01.922 --> 02:07.909
And Leslie got up and shared, and she gave a revelation in that moment, and she shared something that was so strong in that moment.

02:07.929 --> 02:09.831
It was just an awakening to me.

02:09.971 --> 02:12.815
And in that moment, I was like, that needs to be a sermon.

02:12.875 --> 02:14.577
That needs to be developed further.

02:14.997 --> 02:15.798
I need to share this.

02:15.838 --> 02:17.801
So I'm gonna read a little bit of what she has.

02:17.821 --> 02:24.669
And I'm also gonna read a ton of scripture tonight today, but I just want you to know that this was one of those things that just hit me.

02:25.049 --> 02:26.591
And I'll just read what she said.

02:26.691 --> 02:29.074
So she said, we're asking God for more time.

02:29.602 --> 02:32.385
She said, we're asking God for an extension of days.

02:32.485 --> 02:35.008
And she says this, we moved through those early days.

02:35.048 --> 02:38.432
The Holy Spirit very, very clearly spoke to my heart.

02:38.792 --> 02:43.878
And he said, Leslie, do you know what Lazarus's miracle was?

02:44.699 --> 02:47.121
It was simply a miracle of more time.

02:48.383 --> 02:48.803
She shares that.

02:48.823 --> 02:50.966
Like she's praying, she's like, God, give Scott more time.

02:50.986 --> 02:52.127
God, give Scott more time.

02:52.147 --> 02:54.950
And the Holy Spirit speaks and said, I gave Lazarus more time.

02:55.010 --> 02:56.432
God gave Lazarus more time.

02:56.712 --> 02:58.674
And it was just a miracle of more time.

02:59.106 --> 03:01.190
She said, I counter back to God with bewilderment.

03:01.410 --> 03:07.340
And he spoke again, not an audible voice, just a thought with such clarity and providence that it simply couldn't have been my own.

03:08.221 --> 03:13.530
I gave Lazarus more time, Leslie, but he did eventually die.

03:13.570 --> 03:16.175
Well, this is no hidden secret in scripture.

03:16.455 --> 03:19.541
It was a word spoken to me to hold in my heart in this season.

03:20.162 --> 03:25.170
Over the next months, I was able to see that we were living on the gift of Lazarus time.

03:26.018 --> 03:30.647
Scott and I had our eyes open to see these gifts that God was giving to us.

03:31.208 --> 03:32.130
She goes on to say this.

03:32.190 --> 03:38.402
She said, in this world of complexity, with goodness and evil growing up together around us, God is here every single minute.

03:38.683 --> 03:42.129
He hates the evil that happens to his kids, but we have to choose him.

03:42.450 --> 03:46.578
We have to move toward him and ask him, call out to him again and again.

03:46.946 --> 03:53.595
She said, I watched Scott do this at the Mayo as he shared his faith with every single person that entered the room.

03:53.615 --> 04:00.064
He heard God ask and he responded even to the point of making sure that the chaplain at Mayo knew the gospel.

04:01.185 --> 04:02.747
Sometimes you get a checkup on those chaplains.

04:02.767 --> 04:04.610
I'm just saying, all right.

04:04.630 --> 04:06.692
Even when he struggled, he would say to me, or text me.

04:06.733 --> 04:08.815
Again, I'm reading back what Leslie said there.

04:09.717 --> 04:14.823
Even when he struggled, he would say to me, or text me, please pray over me right now, pray for peace.

04:14.843 --> 04:16.786
She closed out by saying this at the funeral.

04:17.730 --> 04:21.476
She said, I wanted to share these moments because I think we all face them daily.

04:21.816 --> 04:23.739
The choice to do or believe the right thing.

04:24.020 --> 04:29.468
We live in a culture that cripples us with decision fatigue, but we can't get carried away by those waves.

04:29.788 --> 04:32.993
We have to plant our feet to listen for the voice of God.

04:33.053 --> 04:36.238
There is so much blessing in the action of obedience.

04:36.679 --> 04:41.847
I want people to know that we learned we need to choose Him in each and every moment.

04:42.648 --> 04:46.674
She went on to say, her husband was that man that was not defined by his circumstances.

04:46.818 --> 04:50.422
He was defined by the choices he made in those circumstances.

04:50.843 --> 04:54.267
He lived for Jesus with his Lazarus time.

04:55.708 --> 04:56.469
And it just hit me.

04:57.550 --> 04:59.352
It was so insightful, so inspiring.

04:59.933 --> 05:07.982
Living on Lazarus time, that God gave Lazarus an extension of life, but eventually he died, and what did he do with that extension?

05:08.223 --> 05:10.846
We're all living on Lazarus time.

05:11.006 --> 05:14.610
Every single one of us is living on Lazarus time.

05:15.042 --> 05:16.064
We're all gonna die.

05:16.104 --> 05:18.769
This world is gonna, for each of us, it's gonna end for each of us.

05:19.069 --> 05:20.993
And what are we gonna do with our Lazarus time?

05:21.013 --> 05:25.380
And if you've had a near-death experience, how many of you know you live a little differently?

05:25.821 --> 05:26.923
I mean, you live a little differently.

05:26.963 --> 05:29.007
I mean, I was going through our family, and I was just thinking like this.

05:29.027 --> 05:31.491
We have a lot of our family living on Lazarus time.

05:31.812 --> 05:35.578
My mom, over 30 years ago, had a bypass surgery.

05:35.859 --> 05:39.986
I believe it was double bypass, and has been living on Lazarus time.

05:40.674 --> 05:43.216
The medical world has given her an extension.

05:43.236 --> 05:46.540
Sometimes you get it through medicine, sometimes you get it through a miracle.

05:46.800 --> 05:51.384
I was thinking about this, my brother Rick and myself had heart attacks within months of each other.

05:51.404 --> 05:52.886
I have three stents in my heart.

05:52.906 --> 05:54.427
I'm living on Lazarus time.

05:54.467 --> 05:57.730
I wake up every day and I realize I'm living on Lazarus time.

05:57.750 --> 06:03.015
My brother Roger was in a head on collision, broke his neck, crushed his skull in a coma.

06:03.035 --> 06:06.278
I had to come back out, learn how to walk and to eat and all these things.

06:06.639 --> 06:09.361
He's still today living on Lazarus time.

06:09.401 --> 06:10.002
Think about it.

06:10.370 --> 06:11.271
You probably have a story.

06:11.291 --> 06:21.442
I mean, I was just with Greg Mundus, a friend of mine, he heads up the Assembys of God World Missions and he was one of the first people in America to get COVID and go on a ventilator.

06:22.203 --> 06:36.178
He was in Missouri and he was one of the first people to get COVID and to not be able to breathe and they put him on a ventilator and for 40 days, he was in a coma on a ventilator and we as a church and as a nation, interceded and prayed for him to live

06:36.290 --> 06:39.093
And after 40 days, he came out of the coma.

06:39.113 --> 06:43.158
I was with him last week and he said, I just feel like I'm living on renewed time.

06:43.198 --> 06:45.120
Like, what does God want me to do with this time?

06:45.361 --> 06:47.824
And we started talking about you're living on Lazarus time.

06:48.044 --> 06:49.906
He's like, I'm living on Lazarus time.

06:50.987 --> 06:54.171
We all are living on Lazarus time.

06:54.191 --> 06:56.934
If you don't know the story, and I know this, not everybody knows the story.

06:56.954 --> 06:58.156
So I'm gonna go there and I'm gonna read it.

06:58.416 --> 07:00.178
And like I said, I'm gonna read a lot here today.

07:00.994 --> 07:04.439
In John chapter 11, verse one, a man named Lazarus was sick.

07:04.500 --> 07:06.843
He lived in Bethany with his sisters, Mary and Martha.

07:06.883 --> 07:11.431
This is the Mary who later poured the expensive perfume on the Lord's feet and wiped them with her hair.

07:11.711 --> 07:13.153
Her brother Lazarus was sick.

07:13.474 --> 07:17.781
So the two sisters sent a message to Jesus telling him, Lord, your dear friend is very sick.

07:18.301 --> 07:21.727
But when Jesus heard about it, he said, Lazarus sickness will not end in death.

07:22.007 --> 07:26.194
No, it happened for the glory of God so that the son of God will see glory from this.

07:26.466 --> 07:31.332
So although Jesus loved Martha, Mary, and Lazarus, he stayed where he was for the next two days.

07:31.453 --> 07:34.456
Finally, he said to his disciples, let's go back to Judea.

07:34.717 --> 07:35.758
But his disciples objected.

07:35.878 --> 07:39.763
Rabbi, they said, only a few days ago the people in Judea were trying to stone you.

07:40.404 --> 07:41.285
Are you going there again?

07:41.325 --> 07:42.106
Isn't that interesting?

07:42.447 --> 07:45.491
The disciples are like, Jesus, by the way, they're trying to kill you.

07:45.591 --> 07:47.153
Do you want to go back there?

07:47.173 --> 07:47.754
We don't want to go back.

07:47.774 --> 07:48.275
Do you want to go back?

07:48.675 --> 07:49.136
Do you want to go back?

07:49.216 --> 07:49.396
I do.

07:49.536 --> 07:50.057
I'm going back.

07:50.357 --> 07:52.500
Jesus never let fear of man stop him.

07:53.261 --> 07:54.002
And neither should you.

07:54.658 --> 07:56.300
Okay, continuing on, let's go to verse 17.

07:56.781 --> 08:01.787
When Jesus arrived at Bethany, he was told that Lazarus had already been in the grave for four days.

08:02.227 --> 08:08.275
Bethany was only a few miles down the road from Jerusalem, and many of the people had come to console Martha and Mary in their loss.

08:08.315 --> 08:11.819
When Martha got the word that Jesus was coming, she went to meet him.

08:11.880 --> 08:12.961
But Mary stayed in the house.

08:13.061 --> 08:17.547
Martha said to Jesus, Lord, if only you had been here, my brother would not have died.

08:17.907 --> 08:20.671
But even now, I know that God will give you whatever you ask.

08:20.751 --> 08:23.474
Jesus told her, your brother will rise again.

08:23.650 --> 08:26.935
Yes, Martha said, he will rise when everyone else rises at the last day.

08:26.995 --> 08:30.520
Jesus told her, I am the resurrection and the life.

08:30.900 --> 08:34.646
Anyone who believes in me will live even after dying.

08:36.008 --> 08:38.211
Everyone who lives in me and believes in me will never die.

08:38.411 --> 08:39.413
Do you believe this, Martha?

08:39.573 --> 08:45.842
Yes, Lord, she told him, I have always believed you are the Messiah, the Son of God, the one who has come into the world, world from God.

08:46.434 --> 08:47.295
Then she returned to Mary.

08:47.315 --> 08:51.260
She called Mary aside from the mourners and told her, the teacher is here and wants to see you.

08:51.280 --> 08:52.481
So Mary immediately went to him.

08:52.521 --> 08:55.725
Jesus had stayed outside the village at the place where Martha met him.

08:56.185 --> 09:02.152
When the people who were out the house, consoling Mary saw her leave so hastily, they assumed she was going to Lazarus grave to weep.

09:02.433 --> 09:03.374
So they followed her there.

09:03.894 --> 09:06.217
When Martha arrived, again, I said, it's a lot of scripture.

09:06.237 --> 09:10.322
When Martha arrived and saw Jesus, she fell at his feet and said, Lord, if only

09:10.722 --> 09:15.894
You had been here, my brother would not have died when Jesus saw her weeping and saw the other people wailing with her.

09:16.034 --> 09:20.103
A deep anger welled up within him and he was deeply troubled.

09:20.404 --> 09:21.466
Where have you put him?

09:22.047 --> 09:26.738
He asked them and they told him, Lord, come and see, then Jesus wept.

09:27.074 --> 09:31.400
The people were standing nearby, said, see how much he loved him, but some said this man healed a blind man.

09:31.661 --> 09:33.123
Couldn't he have kept Lazarus from dying?

09:33.383 --> 09:36.447
Jesus was still angry as he arrived at the tomb.

09:36.748 --> 09:38.691
A cave with a stone rolled across its entrance.

09:38.991 --> 09:40.774
Roll the stone aside, Jesus told them.

09:40.794 --> 09:42.676
But Martha, the dead man's sister, protested.

09:42.736 --> 09:44.659
Lord, he has been dead for four days.

09:44.980 --> 09:46.642
The smell will be terrible.

09:46.978 --> 09:50.325
Jesus responded, didn't I tell you that you would see God's glory if you believe?

09:50.625 --> 09:51.888
So they rolled the stone aside.

09:51.928 --> 09:55.034
Then Jesus looked up to heaven and said, Father, thank you for hearing me.

09:55.074 --> 09:56.217
You always hear me.

09:56.537 --> 09:57.840
Wow, that's just an amazing thought.

09:58.161 --> 09:59.363
You always hear me.

09:59.964 --> 10:04.393
But I said it out loud for the sake of these people standing here so that they will believe you sent me.

10:04.413 --> 10:06.738
Then Jesus shouted, Lazarus, come out.

10:07.458 --> 10:11.864
And the dead man came out, his hands and feet bound in grave clothes, his face wrapped in a headcloth.

10:12.084 --> 10:13.887
Jesus told them, unwrap him and let him go.

10:13.927 --> 10:18.092
Many of the people who were there with Mary believed in Jesus when they saw this happen.

10:18.132 --> 10:18.913
I had to read that.

10:19.214 --> 10:22.038
I thought about summarizing it, but I love God's word too much.

10:24.180 --> 10:25.382
A couple of things, a couple of things.

10:25.462 --> 10:28.306
Now these are not the main point of the sermon, but I can't miss them.

10:28.610 --> 10:30.232
God's timing and our timing are not the same.

10:30.533 --> 10:33.057
Jesus stays a few days and it's so confusing to everybody.

10:33.317 --> 10:38.184
And I'll tell you this, if you serve Jesus long enough, you will understand His timing and your timing are not the same, all right?

10:38.504 --> 10:40.247
It will confuse you, okay?

10:41.429 --> 10:42.971
Jesus can handle your if-only's.

10:43.011 --> 10:44.633
That's why I said if-only, if-only.

10:44.894 --> 10:50.482
He can handle your if-only's, but you gotta let go of your if-only's and trust Jesus, all right?

10:50.658 --> 10:51.879
I love that Jesus cried.

10:51.980 --> 10:55.524
I won't dwell on that, but I love that He cried because it shows humanity.

10:55.564 --> 10:56.525
It shows compassion.

10:56.805 --> 10:57.807
It shows a realness.

10:57.867 --> 10:59.489
It didn't just go like a robot.

10:59.529 --> 11:01.872
He had compassion and He felt the pain.

11:03.814 --> 11:06.257
I love this, too, that the four days is significant.

11:06.998 --> 11:13.906
They put that in there, that He was dead for four days, and that was significant because the Jewish people believed that the soul of the person that died

11:14.306 --> 11:17.149
For three days we try to come back into the body.

11:17.450 --> 11:20.933
For three days we try to get back in, but four days it's over.

11:20.993 --> 11:27.401
For three days there'd be a hope that maybe somebody could come back, but four days not a chance.

11:28.001 --> 11:29.343
So that's important that that's there.

11:29.383 --> 11:39.354
And then I stress the verse 25, because the only reason we can have Lazarus time, let me read it again, is Jesus says this, I'm the resurrection and the life.

11:39.494 --> 11:42.898
Anyone who believes in me will live even after dying.

11:43.714 --> 11:47.378
So whether you've had a near-death experience or not, you have life.

11:47.758 --> 11:51.582
Ephesians talks about that God has moved us from death to life.

11:51.622 --> 11:58.009
When we say yes to Jesus, we move from death to life, and we are living on a new timeframe.

11:58.369 --> 11:59.831
A new clock has started.

12:00.191 --> 12:04.155
We're living on this resurrection life time clock, if you will.

12:05.376 --> 12:10.802
Now the Bible gives us a glimpse of how Lazarus used his time, and so that's where I want to focus today.

12:10.882 --> 12:17.088
And I wanna look at this and contrast it to another person in the Bible that got a life extension.

12:18.910 --> 12:22.633
So Lazarus, we see this that he gets this life extension.

12:22.693 --> 12:27.398
He's back from the dead and the Bible tells us this about Lazarus.

12:27.418 --> 12:28.960
All that was just the introduction, all right?

12:28.980 --> 12:31.222
The Bible tells us this about Lazarus.

12:31.302 --> 12:32.683
John chapter 12, verse nine.

12:32.923 --> 12:39.730
When all the people heard of Jesus' arrival, they flocked to see him and also to see Lazarus.

12:40.162 --> 12:42.024
The man Jesus had raised from the dead.

12:42.344 --> 12:51.112
Then the leading priest decided to kill Lazarus too, for it was because of him that many of the people had deserted them and believed in Jesus.

12:51.993 --> 13:00.501
You may not realize this, but Lazarus was so effective living on Lazarus time that the leaders wanted to kill him.

13:01.422 --> 13:04.224
I mean, could you imagine you were already dead?

13:05.085 --> 13:10.130
Jesus breaks you back from the dead and now there's a bounty on your head.

13:12.386 --> 13:16.411
The only reason there is a bounty was because he wouldn't shut his mouth.

13:17.493 --> 13:18.855
He's like, hey, I'm the guy.

13:19.095 --> 13:19.796
He did it.

13:20.156 --> 13:20.917
He's the one.

13:20.937 --> 13:21.819
I was dead.

13:22.279 --> 13:23.501
Can you imagine?

13:24.162 --> 13:25.804
He was so effective.

13:25.824 --> 13:27.266
And I just want to share this with you.

13:27.606 --> 13:42.386
If you and I are living on Lazarus time, if you've actually been given an extension through meat like my heart stents or you beat cancer or you beat something and you had a miracle in your life, you are living on double Lazarus time.

13:42.498 --> 13:44.100
Don't close your mouth.

13:45.883 --> 13:56.879
Open your mouth, and even if you didn't have that, you were dead, and now you're alive, and you should be out there talking and sharing, and you should be so effective that people are like, we gotta shut that person up.

13:58.802 --> 14:03.389
Praise God they don't wanna kill us, but they wanted to kill him, and they're like, they're coming after him.

14:03.649 --> 14:07.255
Now, because here's the thing, miracles are hard to argue with.

14:09.118 --> 14:12.082
Now I cannot believe you're a miracle, I can do that.

14:12.738 --> 14:16.883
But it's hard for me to argue against your miracle.

14:17.264 --> 14:18.065
Imagine Lazarus.

14:19.146 --> 14:19.646
I was dead.

14:20.447 --> 14:21.529
Well, like, were you dead?

14:21.669 --> 14:23.491
I mean, were you like, mostly dead?

14:23.511 --> 14:25.694
I mean, because there's a difference between mostly dead and dead.

14:25.814 --> 14:28.197
I mean, I mean, no, no, I was dead dead.

14:28.718 --> 14:31.241
Like, I was four days dead.

14:31.321 --> 14:32.703
I was stinky dead.

14:34.625 --> 14:36.367
That's my sister, either one.

14:37.609 --> 14:39.211
I was dead, okay?

14:39.431 --> 14:42.034
And so there are, you can argue,

14:42.114 --> 14:43.397
It's like, how do you argue?

14:43.417 --> 14:44.420
Like, okay, he was dead.

14:44.981 --> 14:46.164
They're all saying he was dead.

14:46.184 --> 14:49.172
So you might leave pondering, but share your miracle.

14:49.192 --> 14:49.753
Can I tell you this?

14:49.814 --> 14:50.676
Share your miracle.

14:51.799 --> 14:52.681
Share your miracle.

14:53.423 --> 14:55.087
Who were you before Christ found you?

14:55.428 --> 14:56.471
Share your miracle.

14:56.731 --> 14:58.416
You're on Lazarus time right now.

14:58.436 --> 14:59.378
We all are.

14:59.490 --> 15:01.433
I mean, God took you from death to life.

15:01.533 --> 15:02.414
Share your miracle.

15:02.474 --> 15:04.618
Maybe you were addicted and God set you free.

15:04.918 --> 15:06.520
Share your miracle.

15:06.861 --> 15:09.244
Maybe you were materialistic and you were caught up into it.

15:09.285 --> 15:10.526
All of a sudden God set you free.

15:11.027 --> 15:11.828
Change your life.

15:12.149 --> 15:13.731
Share your miracle.

15:15.033 --> 15:21.603
After I had my heart attack in 2014, and the three stones put in, I couldn't help but share my miracle.

15:22.043 --> 15:26.450
Every time we got to eat and the server come up, what do you want to eat?

15:26.562 --> 15:30.288
Anything that tastes good because a couple of weeks ago, I almost died.

15:30.569 --> 15:32.352
And my family would be like, oh, here he goes again.

15:32.472 --> 15:32.752
All right.

15:33.974 --> 15:35.176
I was like, I had a heart attack.

15:35.196 --> 15:35.697
I didn't do anything.

15:35.897 --> 15:37.901
And I love Jesus.

15:38.161 --> 15:39.363
And I knew I was going to heaven.

15:39.383 --> 15:42.248
And I'm going to make the most of the time that I've got.

15:42.448 --> 15:43.370
And you should know, too.

15:43.630 --> 15:45.974
And I'll have whatever you just suggested.

15:46.034 --> 15:46.294
All right.

15:47.396 --> 15:48.498
I was just sharing it.

15:49.314 --> 15:52.958
You have to share the miracle over and over.

15:52.978 --> 15:53.838
Be so effective.

15:54.079 --> 15:58.483
Lazarus was so effective they wanted to take him out.

