20:00.058 --> 20:02.221
And the Bible tells us right after this.

20:02.241 --> 20:03.623
He gets a 15 year extension.

20:03.943 --> 20:06.066
The Assyrians are, they're protected from them.

20:06.914 --> 20:19.110
And in his 15 year extension, instead of being so bold for God that people want to kill him, instead of like being all about the things of God, Hezekiah does the opposite of Lazarus.

20:20.192 --> 20:23.296
Hezekiah becomes all about Hezekiah.

20:24.898 --> 20:27.922
And he starts saying, aren't I something special?

20:28.354 --> 20:42.195
And the Bible shows us right there in 2 Kings 20 verse 13, Hezekiah received the Babylonian envoys and showed them everything in his treasure houses, the silver, the gold, the spices and the aromatic oils.

20:42.615 --> 20:46.701
He also took them to see his armory and showed them everything in his royal treasuries.

20:47.022 --> 20:50.787
There is nothing in his palace or kingdom that Hezekiah didn't show them.

20:51.549 --> 20:52.530
Do you get the picture?

20:53.314 --> 20:56.197
Lazarus is like, Jesus, Jesus, he healed me.

20:56.397 --> 20:58.880
I was dead, Jesus, Jesus, Jesus.

20:59.040 --> 21:03.225
Hezekiah gets an extension and he's like, look at what I have.

21:04.527 --> 21:05.688
Look at how great I am.

21:06.389 --> 21:07.490
Look at all the gold.

21:07.910 --> 21:13.096
God gave me an extension and I took this wisdom and I'm making more money and more stuff.

21:13.116 --> 21:14.398
