21:19.330 --> 21:20.814
And then it gets even sadder.

21:20.834 --> 21:23.321
I mean, he's living the opposite of Lazarus.

21:23.341 --> 21:27.232
It gets even sadder in 2 Kings verse 19, chapter 20.

21:27.613 --> 21:29.458
Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah,

21:29.730 --> 21:31.332
So Isaiah says to him, come, sorry.

21:31.552 --> 21:33.515
He says, everything you have now is going to be taken away.

21:33.615 --> 21:34.656
