22:07.976 --> 22:12.784
All the gold that belongs to God and the silver and the oils and all this stuff that's been accumulated.

22:13.105 --> 22:15.449
Another king is gonna come in and ransack it.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.152
But you know what Hezekiah says?

22:19.396 --> 22:21.379
At least for my 15 years it's gonna be okay.

22:23.483 --> 22:25.266
Selfish and pride.

22:25.442 --> 22:30.026
So the exact opposite of what an extension should do to you.

22:30.967 --> 22:32.008
Exact opposite.

22:32.369 --> 22:35.772
And I think about this, how sad that that's the way he lived.

22:36.112 --> 22:45.100
How sad, like I get angry personally, like when I see politicians make a decision that's good for them for 15 months and bad for us for 50 years.

22:46.462 --> 22:55.250
And I see this and I think it's even worse when a Christian has been given Lazarus time or resurrection lifetime and then we live selfish.

22:55.874 --> 23:01.604
And with a prideful, and God's like, I've given you all this, I want you to live for me, I want you to open your mouth, I want you to share the miracle.

23:01.905 --> 23:06.633
And instead we live a life, like look at my toys, look at my stuff, look at how great my life is.

23:06.914 --> 23:14.287
Well, at least it doesn't affect me, it'll just affect my kids and my grandkids if I don't go to church that often and don't pass on the faith.

23:15.509 --> 23:18.514
How terrible, how terrible.

23:18.722 --> 23:22.908
Every one of us has been given Lazarus time, resurrection and lifetime.

23:23.168 --> 23:25.711
We've been given the opportunity to live differently.

23:27.574 --> 23:30.878
Hezekiah should have lived like, hey guys, guys, you won't believe this.

23:31.579 --> 23:33.462
Welcome to the temple, the gold's nothing, the gold's nothing.

23:33.482 --> 23:34.103
Can I just show you?

23:34.123 --> 23:35.204
I had a boil right here.

23:35.425 --> 23:36.546
Like the boil's gonna kill me.

23:36.566 --> 23:38.308
I was like, it was this thing, it was this thing.

23:38.609 --> 23:41.152
And God took it away and he made me 15 years.

23:41.493 --> 23:43.195
And he's the miracle working God.

23:43.435 --> 23:44.657
Do you want us to pray right now?

23:44.677 --> 23:46.459
But instead he's like, look at the gold.

23:47.661 --> 23:48.402
Look at this stuff.

23:49.250 --> 23:50.712
He missed the message.

23:51.834 --> 23:55.179
He missed, don't get a new life from God.

23:55.319 --> 23:59.625
Don't give, don't get Lazarus time and miss the message.

24:01.708 --> 24:03.751
So sad, so sad.

24:04.072 --> 24:09.039
Our time, our talent, our treasure, our testimony should be for his glory.

24:10.621 --> 24:15.909
Now, I know when I share this, I know what's going on in some people's minds, like, oh boy, I should sell it all.

24:16.530 --> 24:17.211
I don't need a toy.

24:18.233 --> 24:19.154
I should live in a box.

24:19.330 --> 24:21.793
I don't know, I mean, you start thinking like that, okay?

24:22.053 --> 24:23.715
So let me just put this in perspective.

24:24.415 --> 24:34.325
Living on Lazarus time, living with the resurrection lifetime that God has given to all of us, you still are smiling, you still are full of joy.

24:34.586 --> 24:41.172
There was a legend around Lazarus that said he never smiled after he came back from the dead.

24:41.192 --> 24:45.457
The legend, just the people in that era said after Lazarus came back from the dead, he never smiled.

24:45.717 --> 24:46.578
I don't believe that's true.

24:47.298 --> 24:54.327
I don't believe that's true, because when I look in John chapter 12, verses one and two, it says, 6 days before the Passover celebration began, Jesus arrived in Bethany.

24:54.347 --> 24:59.274
This is after Lazarus has come back from the dead, the home of Lazarus, the man he had raised from the dead.

24:59.895 --> 25:01.717
Dinner was prepared in Jesus' honor.

25:02.058 --> 25:05.703
Martha served, and Lazarus was among those who ate with him.

25:06.664 --> 25:08.106
I believe that he was enjoying dinner.

25:08.767 --> 25:11.831
I believe that Lazarus didn't say, Jesus, we don't have time for a dinner party.

25:12.291 --> 25:13.213
We don't have time for this.

25:13.533 --> 25:14.354
It's all serious.

25:14.434 --> 25:17.878
He's like, no, I'm gonna enjoy life in the midst of this.

25:18.319 --> 25:30.073
I'm gonna enjoy what God, what you've given to me, and I'm gonna take time for those festivals and those meals, and I'm gonna use up my vacation, and I'm gonna enjoy these things, but these things don't have me.

25:30.554 --> 25:40.566
I have these things, but they don't have me, and I use them for your glory, and yep, we enjoy time off, and we enjoy looking at the mountains and the ocean, and we enjoy these things, but you know what?

25:41.106 --> 25:41.967
There's joy.

25:41.987 --> 25:44.210
There's life that's there.

25:44.706 --> 25:51.012
I'll tell you why I thought that about some people thinking this way is I was goofing off in church.

25:51.052 --> 25:56.017
I don't know, I was goofing off in church service, but I was goofing off in some church setting.

25:56.798 --> 26:03.264
And I like to have fun, my wife teased me, she's like, you're the yes man, I like to do, yeah, we'll do that, sure, we'll try that too.

26:03.785 --> 26:05.226
Let's go, let's do that.

26:05.587 --> 26:06.368
I'm up for it.

26:06.828 --> 26:12.914
And I was just doing something stupid and goofy, it wasn't bad, but it was just kind of dumb and stupid.

26:13.314 --> 26:17.819
And I can't remember exactly what it was, but I was probably doing it with Pastor Kirk or somebody.

26:17.859 --> 26:19.080
I was just having fun.

26:20.182 --> 26:28.371
And this person in our church goes, I bet your missionary, this part of lived dead, would not behave like you.

26:28.431 --> 26:38.642
Life is so serious and I know that missionary and I bet they would never do anything like you are doing now.

26:38.882 --> 26:39.584
Oh, you have no idea.

26:39.604 --> 26:43.051
And I won't say their name because I just want to protect the, not the person in our church.

26:43.071 --> 26:43.592
I would not do that.

26:43.632 --> 26:44.955
I'm saying the missionary, all right.

26:44.975 --> 26:47.701
I wouldn't say the missionary's name because I want to protect their person's identity.

26:48.303 --> 26:49.425
But I was like, you have no idea.

26:50.026 --> 26:51.169
I've traveled the world with this person.

26:51.750 --> 26:53.554
Like this person pulls jokes all the time.

26:53.794 --> 26:55.756
This person tripped me down the stairs.

26:55.836 --> 26:57.278
Like, I fell down and hurt myself.

26:57.538 --> 26:58.520
And he laughed at me.

26:58.620 --> 26:59.761
Like, I was like, what is that?

27:00.201 --> 27:03.365
You know, I mean, this person fed me bad food and laughed.

27:03.385 --> 27:06.669
Like, I was like, you don't understand.

27:06.689 --> 27:07.750
Like, we have a blast.

27:07.770 --> 27:08.912
Like, we have fun.

27:08.972 --> 27:09.833
We are serious.

27:09.873 --> 27:11.074
We're living on Lazarus time.

27:11.294 --> 27:12.616
And we're making a difference for Jesus.

27:12.656 --> 27:15.079
But when it's time to laugh, we laugh.

27:15.740 --> 27:17.842
Then when it's time to eat, we eat.

27:18.050 --> 27:23.477
We've been so full, we barely get back to the hotel, we're so full, and we're having fun telling stories.

27:23.838 --> 27:25.720
